question.title: java: incompatible types: T cannot be converted to T
question.body:
I was working on a school assignment on generics, when I ran into a really weird error. I'm getting 5 incompatible types errors at compile time, but all of them bar 1 are saying that a type is incompatible with the exact same type.

Here is the code:

public class Utility <T> {

    ArrayList<T> list = new ArrayList<>();

    // Insert the code here.
    public Utility() {
        list = new ArrayList<>();
    }

    public Utility(List<T> list) {
        this.list = new ArrayList<T>(list);
    }

    public <T extends Comparable<T>> int linearSearch(T item) {
        int position = -1;
        for (int i = 0; i < list.size(); i++) {
            if (item.compareTo(list.get(i)) == 0) {
                position = i;
                break;
            }
        }
        return position;
    }

    public <T> void mergeList(List<T> list) {
        for (T obj: this.list)
            list.add(obj);
    }

    public <T> boolean containList(List<T> list) {
        if (this.list.containsAll(list)) {
            this.list = new ArrayList<T>();
            for (T obj: list)
                this.list.add(obj);
            return true;
        }
        else
            return false;
    }

    public <T> void removeZero(List<T> myList) {
        for (int i = 0; i < myList.size(); i++) {
            if (MyInteger.isZero(myList.get(i))) {
                myList.remove(i);
                i--;
            }
        }
    }

}
